column2: The Type column indicates how the row will be used.
#=comment, R=test revision, T=table, S=subtitle, H=header, and X=something on the test
The Label column is the text for whatever the row is (Table title, header, technique, etc). Row is ignored if it’s blank
The Y, O, G, P, b, B, R, T, 1, 2, 3 columns are the configuration for the ranks (Yellow, Orange, etc)
For comments and the test revision, the ranks are ignored.
For Tables and Subtitles, the valid values are:  X=show, blank=don’t show
For Headers:  X=show, C=collapse and only show new techniques, blank=don’t show
For techniques:  X=show, N=show as new technique, blank=don’t show, other=show value in parens
